    <text>
        <body>
            <head>191. Memorandum From the Director of the <orgName corresp="rec0LJhvaDXM7fvRo"
                    >Office of Management and Budget</orgName> (<persName
                    corresp="recwSYRHgMlWvuReF">Lance</persName>) to President <persName
                    corresp="reccm3OnsdQpGeNR8">Carter</persName>
                <note n="1" place="foot" type="source" xml:id="d191fn1">Source: Carter Library,
                    National Security Affairs, Brzezinski Material, Brzezinski Office File, Country
                    Chron File, Box 50, Tunisia. Confidential.</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1977-07-20"
                        >July 20, 1977</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <list type="subject">
                <head>SUBJECT</head>
                <item>Presidential Determination to Waive the Ceiling on <rs type="topic"
                        corresp="recoKawZ2IOcE8nyB">Military Assistance</rs> to <placeName
                        corresp="rech4Y08vWrfyBSYC">Africa</placeName>
                </item>
            </list>
            <p>I concur in Secretary <persName corresp="recRM4qiy2MVhNDPu">Vance</persName>’s
                recommendation that you sign the attached <rs corresp="recKz0w91lnkAu1cS"
                    type="topic">determination</rs> waiving the $40 million ceiling on <rs
                    type="topic" corresp="recoKawZ2IOcE8nyB">military assistance</rs> (including
                grants, credits, and loan guarantees) for <placeName corresp="rech4Y08vWrfyBSYC"
                    >Africa</placeName> in fiscal year 1977.<note n="2" place="foot"
                    xml:id="d191fn2">Not attached. For <persName corresp="recRM4qiy2MVhNDPu"
                        >Vance</persName>’s recommendation, see <ref target="#d190">Document
                        190</ref>.</note>
            </p>
            <p>This determination is necessary, since the <rs type="event"
                    corresp="rec2z1tbfKZPT8edv">Administration</rs>’s proposed 1977 budget levels
                for the eight African countries exceed $40 million, and the <orgName
                    corresp="recmLoDjMiF4yt3cM">Congress</orgName> has not agreed to eliminate the
                ceiling provision in current <rs type="topic" corresp="recfsYEHWUfhmWQY2">security
                    assistance</rs> legislation.</p>
            <p>By approving this <rs corresp="recKz0w91lnkAu1cS" type="topic">determination</rs> and
                transmitting the required justifications to <orgName corresp="recmLoDjMiF4yt3cM"
                    >Congress</orgName>, you would also be approving an increase in fiscal 1977
                    <gloss target="#t_FMS_1">
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="recM6MmQNEwIZpchW">FMS</rs>
                </gloss> financing for <placeName corresp="recGkuSlDiu6KVzHj">Tunisia</placeName>
                from the budgeted $15 million to $25 million. The amounts shown for all other
                planned country programs in the attached table<note n="3" place="foot"
                    xml:id="d191fn3">Not attached.</note> were previously approved and reflected in
                the 1978 <orgName corresp="recmLoDjMiF4yt3cM">Congressional</orgName> Presentation
                    document.<note n="4" place="foot" xml:id="d191fn4">Not found.</note>
            </p>
            <p>The <placeName corresp="recGkuSlDiu6KVzHj">Tunisian</placeName> increase would be
                used to accelerate delivery of the integrated air defense system (Chaparral missile
                batteries, radar, and Vulcan anti-aircraft guns) which <rs type="compound-subject"
                    corresp="recvVLlMQyjpyiiF9">Tunisia</rs> has begun purchasing to meet what it
                perceives to be an increased threat from <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH"
                    >Libya</placeName>. This increase for <placeName corresp="recGkuSlDiu6KVzHj"
                    >Tunisia</placeName> is not likely to raise questions about your overall policy
                of restraint in <rs type="topic" corresp="rec9ptkWICFUk7Mvu">arms transfers</rs>,
                since the 1978 <gloss target="#t_FMS_1">
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="recM6MmQNEwIZpchW">FMS</rs>
                </gloss> credit program nearing final approval by the <orgName
                    corresp="recmLoDjMiF4yt3cM">Congress</orgName> includes $25 million for
                    <placeName corresp="recGkuSlDiu6KVzHj">Tunisia</placeName>.</p>
            <p>Funds are currently available for this reallocation, but <gloss target="#t_OMB_1">
                    <orgName corresp="rec0LJhvaDXM7fvRo">OMB</orgName>
                </gloss> believes such increases should have Presidential approval. Accordingly, if
                you agree, your approval of this increase will be conveyed to <orgName
                    corresp="rec7Bg5QUDG0eHqgl">State</orgName> when you sign the Presidential
                Determination for the ceiling waiver.<note n="5" place="foot" xml:id="d191fn5">
                    <persName corresp="reccm3OnsdQpGeNR8">Carter</persName> checked and initialed
                    the option to approve an additional $10 million for <placeName
                        corresp="recGkuSlDiu6KVzHj">Tunisia</placeName>.</note>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
